The actor was then married to Miss 
Hill for seven years, and had two daughters. Soon after they split, he 
confirmed he was dating Miss Cruttenden, who he met on the set of 
Sharpe. They had a daughter in 1998 but divorced two years later.

Last year the actor said that he had finally given up on marriage, saying he preferred spending his time gardening.

‘Of course I believe in love despite 
four divorces. There is nobody who doesn’t believe in love,’ he said. 
‘But marriage – that fits some people but obviously not me. I love doing
just nothing in my free time. I love to be with my kid in Yorkshire. I 
love it there. Working in a garden calms me down.’

Last year Bean was ‘stabbed’ in the 
arm outside a North London pub following a row over glamour model April 
Summers, who is 30 years his junior.

He suffered a cut arm and a bruised face, according to witnesses, but declined to attend hospital

