Instead, the star walked back into the bar and, after staff gave him treatment from a first aid kit, ordered another drink.

A Scotland Yard spokesman said: ‘A 53-year-old man attended a London 
police station for a pre-arranged interview. He was bailed pending 
further inquiries. He was arrested on suspicion of harassment.’

The Daily Mail was unable to contact Bean at his home for a comment yesterday.

A man who answered the intercom at the town house said the actor was not at the address.

Bean’s representatives were not available for comment.

